{"title":"DJI Osmo Action 4 camera Lights Up w/ Massive New Sensor","link":"https://bikerumor.com/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-lights-up-w-massive-new-sensor/","date":1691013259000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2342\" height=\"1597\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-1.jpg\" alt=\"DJI Osmo Action 4 camera shown in water\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-1.jpg 2342w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-1-297x203.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-1-800x546.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-1-120x82.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-1-768x524.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-1-1536x1047.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-1-2048x1397.jpg 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>With GoPro, Insta360, and DJI all having similar stabilization, 4k frame rates, and shooting modes, the one thing a brand needs to win the action camera wars, it’s better low-light image quality. The best way to do that is increasing sensor size, and that’s exactly what the new DJI Osmo Action 4 did.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Compared to<a href=\"https://www.pjatr.com/t/8-12501-131878-218522?website=327165&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fgopro.com%2Fen%2Fus%2Fshop%2Fcameras%2Fhero11-black%2FCHDHX-111-master.html\" target=\"_blank\"> GoPro HERO 11 Black</a> (1/1.9″ sensor) and <a href=\"https://www.insta360.com/product/insta360-oners\" target=\"_blank\">Insta360 ONE RS</a> (1/2″ sensor), that’s massive – 46% bigger than HERO 11, and 65% bigger than their Action 3. DJI seems to take full advantage of that by jumping up to 10-bit D-Log M color (same as HERO 11), meaning it should capture all of the color and way more light than anything else on the market as of August 2023.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-GPS-bluetooth-remote.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1352\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-GPS-bluetooth-remote.jpg\" alt=\"DJI Osmo Action 4 camera shown with GPS bluetooth remote on a MTB handlebar\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-GPS-bluetooth-remote.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-GPS-bluetooth-remote-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-GPS-bluetooth-remote-800x601.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-GPS-bluetooth-remote-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-GPS-bluetooth-remote-768x577.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-GPS-bluetooth-remote-1536x1154.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Other new features include an optional GPS Bluetooth Remote that adds more data (location, speed, elevation) to your video and, obvi, lets you start and stop recording remotely.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-4.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1244\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-4.jpg\" alt=\"DJI Osmo Action 4 camera shown on chest strap\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-4.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-4-297x205.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-4-800x553.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-4-120x83.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-4-768x531.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-4-1536x1062.jpg 1536w\" /></a><figcaption>For best results, mount the camera upside down so you can adjust it to a better angle.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It attaches to their excellent magnetic mounts, of which there are plenty of options, but there’s a new Horizontal/Vertical (H/V) Protective Frame that lets you attach the camera vertically, too. Once snapped into place vertically, it’ll natively record vertical video so you can bump your Stories and TikToks to the next level without having to do any post-production cropping. Just pull the video straight from the camera to your phone with their app and watch those likes swarm in.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-5.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1385\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-5.jpg\" alt=\"DJI Osmo Action 4 camera shown on bicycle saddle rail mount\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-5.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-5-297x229.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-5-800x616.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-5-120x92.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-5-768x591.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-5-1536x1182.jpg 1536w\" /></a><figcaption>If you run this mount with long travel suspension, add their DJI Care Refresh extended warranty for up to two replacements per year.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It keeps their impressive -20° to 45° C (-4° to 113° F) operating range, and they say the battery is protected enough to give you up to 150 minutes of recording at the bottom end of that range. It charges quickly, getting 80% full in just 18 minutes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-3.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1470\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-3.jpg\" alt=\"DJI Osmo Action 4 camera shown on MTB helmet\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-3.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-3-297x243.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-3-800x653.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-3-120x98.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-3-768x627.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-3-1536x1254.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Lastly, waterproofness increases to 18m from 16m without any extra case needed.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-base-kit.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-base-kit.jpg\" alt=\"DJI Osmo Action 4 camera base kit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-base-kit.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-base-kit-297x238.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-base-kit-800x640.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-base-kit-120x96.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-base-kit-768x614.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-base-kit-1536x1229.jpg 1536w\" /></a><figcaption>DJI Action 4 base kit.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Other tech features are fairly standard now and include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>120fps high frame rate in 1080p, 2.7K 16:9, and 4K 16:9</li>\n\n\n\n<li>4K60fps with 155º ultra-wide FOV</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Hydrophobic coating on lens and screens</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Up to 2.5 hours recording time</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Auto Color Balance even adjusts for underwater filming</li>\n\n\n\n<li>RockSteady 3.0 image stabilization</li>\n\n\n\n<li>360º horizon leveling</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Invisible Selfie Stick mode</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-adventure-kit.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"933\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-adventure-kit.jpg\" alt=\"DJI Osmo Action 4 camera adventure kit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-adventure-kit.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-adventure-kit-297x154.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-adventure-kit-800x415.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-adventure-kit-120x62.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-adventure-kit-768x398.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-adventure-kit-1536x796.jpg 1536w\" /></a><figcaption>The Adventure Package is worth the extra $100.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The standard package (<a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0C783YNW7/?tag=20br-20\" target=\"_blank\">$399</a>) includes the camera, their extreme battery, H/V protective frame, quick release adapter mount, adhesive base, mounting screw, charging/sync cable, lens hood, and anti-slip pad. An Adventure Combo ($499) adds two more batteries, an extension handle, a battery case, and a few other bits. Available now.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.dji.com/osmo-action-4\" target=\"_blank\">DJI.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/dji-osmo-action-4-camera-lights-up-w-massive-new-sensor/\">DJI Osmo Action 4 camera Lights Up w/ Massive New Sensor</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"3085633b60b715f526db2b6e4bfecdcccca3694401b4ef321cb8ebac2d7e68f0","category":"Cycling"}